{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/comments/349732891", "html_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4054#issuecomment-349732891", "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4054", "id": 349732891, "node_id": "MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDM0OTczMjg5MQ==", "user": {"login": "colesbury", "id": 655866, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjY1NTg2Ng==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars1.githubusercontent.com/u/655866?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury", "html_url": "https://github.com/colesbury", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/colesbury/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "created_at": "2017-12-06T18:34:05Z", "updated_at": "2017-12-06T18:34:05Z", "author_association": "MEMBER", "body_html": "<p>This looks like a bug in the implementation of <code>repeat</code> to me. These lines look suspicious:</p>\n<p><div class=\"border rounded-1 my-2\">\n  <div class=\"f6 px-3 py-2 lh-condensed border-bottom bg-gray-light\">\n    <p class=\"mb-0 text-bold\">\n      <a href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/38f13447bce8b7dfe925664c2ef7e42659551cb4/torch/tensor.py#L277-L283\">pytorch/torch/tensor.py</a>\n    </p>\n    <p class=\"mb-0 text-gray-light\">\n        Lines 277 to 283\n      in\n      <a data-pjax=\"true\" class=\"commit-tease-sha\" href=\"/pytorch/pytorch/commit/38f13447bce8b7dfe925664c2ef7e42659551cb4\">38f1344</a>\n    </p>\n    </div>\n    <div itemprop=\"text\" class=\"blob-wrapper blob-wrapper-embedded data\">\n    <table class=\"highlight tab-size mb-0 js-file-line-container\" data-tab-size=\"8\">\n\n        <tbody><tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L277\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"277\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC277\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> xtensor <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> src.new().set_(src) </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L278\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"278\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC278\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> xsize <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">list</span>(xtensor.size()) </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L279\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"279\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC279\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> <span class=\"pl-k\">for</span> i <span class=\"pl-k\">in</span> _range(<span class=\"pl-c1\">len</span>(repeats) <span class=\"pl-k\">-</span> src.dim()): </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L280\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"280\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC280\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\">     xsize <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> [<span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>] <span class=\"pl-k\">+</span> xsize </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L281\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"281\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC281\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\">  </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L282\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"282\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC282\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> size <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.Size([a <span class=\"pl-k\">*</span> b <span class=\"pl-k\">for</span> a, b <span class=\"pl-k\">in</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">zip</span>(xsize, repeats)]) </td>\n        </tr>\n\n        <tr class=\"border-0\">\n          <td id=\"L283\" class=\"blob-num border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white js-line-number\" data-line-number=\"283\"></td>\n          <td id=\"LC283\" class=\"blob-code border-0 px-3 py-0 bg-white blob-code-inner js-file-line\"> xtensor.resize_(torch.Size(xsize)) </td>\n        </tr>\n    </tbody></table>\n  </div>\n</div>\n</p>\n<p>We shouldn't be resizing the original storage. We should create a new tensor of the correct size instead.</p>", "body_text": "This looks like a bug in the implementation of repeat to me. These lines look suspicious:\n\n  \n    \n      pytorch/torch/tensor.py\n    \n    \n        Lines 277 to 283\n      in\n      38f1344\n    \n    \n    \n    \n\n        \n          \n           xtensor = src.new().set_(src) \n        \n\n        \n          \n           xsize = list(xtensor.size()) \n        \n\n        \n          \n           for i in _range(len(repeats) - src.dim()): \n        \n\n        \n          \n               xsize = [1] + xsize \n        \n\n        \n          \n            \n        \n\n        \n          \n           size = torch.Size([a * b for a, b in zip(xsize, repeats)]) \n        \n\n        \n          \n           xtensor.resize_(torch.Size(xsize)) \n        \n    \n  \n\n\nWe shouldn't be resizing the original storage. We should create a new tensor of the correct size instead.", "body": "This looks like a bug in the implementation of `repeat` to me. These lines look suspicious:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/blob/38f13447bce8b7dfe925664c2ef7e42659551cb4/torch/tensor.py#L277-L283\r\n\r\nWe shouldn't be resizing the original storage. We should create a new tensor of the correct size instead. "}